<p>In July, 1673, the ship was declared lost by the Commission and was stricken from their records of available vessels. There is very little documentation in the record regarding the <em>Voyager</em> specifically, and the only other Commission record of note is a letter written in 1674 by one of the Commission's Stewards to the Commissioner, Othaniel Trower.</p>
